</P>
<P>
   But no one can be certain either how big the impact will be or
how long it will last. That depends on what happens in Asia.
</P>
<P>
   The Asia effect may seem a distant concern to many Americans;
but some of them, such as farmers, are clearly suffering from it.
</P>
<P>
   The farms depend far more on exports than the rest of the
economy: around 30 percent of farm products are sent overseas,
compared with 13 percent for the economy as a whole.
</P>
<P>
   Until this year East Asia provided a big, and growing, market.
