 &HT;    Why these girls?
 &HT;    Sidebar to TEEN-MODEL
 &HT;    By Cara Anna
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Seventeen's beauty director, Liz Brous, looked over photos of
the eight finalists and explained what got them to New York.
</P>
<P>
   Allison Willis, 16, Port St. Lucie: ``She looked like a really
happy, cool girl. She looked real experimental. She said she cut
off her hair on April Fools' Day. She looks like that kind of
person.''
</P>
<P>
   Erin Sweers, 17, Iowa: ``Look at her fine hair and freckles. She
sent us these teeny school pictures. She looked so fresh and
beautiful.''
</P>
<P>
   Hannah Borum, 15, Maryland: ``We loved her smile. We don't want
them cold and model-y looking. You can tell by her smile how she
would be in front of the camera.''
</P>
<P>
   Samantha Harris, 18, Texas: ``We wanted curly hair. We loved it,
just had to have the hair. We didn't want the readers to think you
have to have stick-straight hair.''
</P>
<P>
   Mila Williams, 15, California: ``A great smile, and such
beautiful skin. One of her parents is from the Philippines.''
</P>
<P>
   Sheena Lutes, 16, Georgia: ``We needed at least somebody blonde
and blue-eyed.''
</P>
<P>
   Leslie Elcyzyn, 18, Oklahoma: ``The freckles. We get a lot of
letters about freckles. She has an interesting look that really
struck everyone. Those almond-shaped eyes.''
</P>
<P>
   Ashleigh Borman, 15, Texas: ``She looks like a girl Seventeen
uses as a model already. She definitely has potential.''
</P>
