   TOBACCO-LAWSUIT _ Attorney General Dan Morales announces final
agreement in Texas' landmark tobacco lawsuit. We seek specifics on
what's next. How much money will the state get, when and where will
the money be spent? (Hight, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   SIXMONTHS _ On the eve of his official installation as president
of the Southern Christian Leadership Conference, Martin Luther King
III talks about the six months that have passed since he was named
to head the organization his father founded. An immediate challenge
is dealing with the fallout from the SCLC board's decision to sever
ties to SCLC Women, which happened in April but just recently
became public knowledge. (Byrd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-DAMS -- Substandard dams pose a growing threat to people
and property in Texas, and the state's inspection program to keep
track of the problem is woefully inadequate, according to a report
by a special task force. (Haurwitz, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
