   JAPAN-OBUCHI (Tokyo) _ Keizo Obuchi, Japan's congenial but
colorless foreign minister, was elected as president of the ruling
Liberal Democratic Party and thereby in line to become prime
minister, dashing the hopes$of those who saw a glimmer of political
reform in the selection process. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   ( With
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-OBUCHI-PROFILE (Tokyo) _ For someone who has been plying
the treacherous waters of Japanese politics since 1963, Keizo
Obuchi has made scarcely a ripple&AMP; He is not identified with any
major government policies, has fo memorable personality traits, and
has not been tarred by any scandals. Yet political experts here say
it is precisely Obuchi's unobtrusive style that brought him to the
top of Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party and has made him the
designated successor to Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto. By Mark
Landler.
</P>
