   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEDICAL-SAVINGS (Washington) _ Medical savings accounts are part
of the Republican legislative prescription for managed health care,
but Democrats say they are a ``poison pill'' that could sour any
chance of compromise on a bill this year. We explore the tangled
controversy. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-WORLDS (Athens, Greece) _ We preview of the World
Championships of Basketball tournament, which begins Wednesday with
Houston Rockets coach Rudy Tomjanovich leading a team of no-names
from the United States against international competitors. By EDDIE
SEFKO.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-VETS (New Orleans) _ Two unlikely names dot the roster of
the New Orleans Zephyrs in former major-leaguers Pete Incaviglia
and Casey Candaele. But both of these former Houston Astros
veterans may prove helpful to the parent team down the stretch. By
NEIL HOHLFELD.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-MINORS (New Orleans) _ As the Houston Astros head into the
stretch run of the pennant race, they will be looking to the minor
leagues for help to shore up the roster. A look at who the top
prospects are at the Triple-A team in New Orleans. By NEIL
HOHLFELD.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Chief Justice William Rehnquist's
decision July 17 to permit testimony of Secret Service agents
before Kenneth Starr's grand jury investigating President Clinton
recalls a Supreme Court decision made 24 years ago this month. It
was a key event that led to the demise of Richard Nixon. By ROBERT
E. THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday)
</P>
<P>
   For Monday:
</P>
<P>
   CHILDREN (Washington) _ In a generation, the number of children
living with mothers who have never married has jumped nearly
five-fold, according to a Census Bureau report being released
Monday at 12:01 a.m. EDT. Mothers raising children alone now care
for nearly a fourth of the children under 18. By NICOLE TSONG.
</P>
