<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S BUSINESS EVENTS CALENDAR  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, JULY 26) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONDAY: The National Association of Realtors reports on home
resales for June. An annual rate of 4.84 million is expected, up
20,000 from May.
</P>
<P>
   The Agriculture Department reports on 1998 crop conditions for
wheat, corn, soybeans and cotton.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY: The Conference Board releases its consumer confidence
index for July. The forecast is for a decrease of 1.7 points, to
135.9.
</P>
<P>
   LJR Redbook Research releases its weekly retail sales survey.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY: The Commerce Department reports on durable-goods
orders for June. A drop of 0.8 percent is expected.
</P>
<P>
   Mitsubishi Bank-Schroder Wertheim releases its weekly retail
sales report. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY: The Commerce Department reports on new-home sales for
June. The forecast is for an increase of 10,000, to 891,000.
</P>
<P>
   The Labor Department reports on weekly unemployment claims.
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY: The Commerce Department reports its preliminary estimate
of economic growth for the second quarter. The average forecast is
for 0.1 percent growth at an annual rate.
</P>
<P>
   The Chicago Purchasing Managers Association releases its
manufacturing index for July. A decrease of 2.1, to 50.8, is
expected.
</P>
