   WATER-PURIFYER _ PALM CITY, Fla. _ Diane Haskett is taking her
late husband's water-purifying invention into new territory.
Haskett's water-treatment products company, Chlorinators Inc. in
Palm City, will renovate and move into 14,600 square feet at the
former Harrison Electric building in downtown Stuart, Fla., by
January. Chlorinator's international marketing affiliate, Regal
Systems International, in which she owns 50 percent interest, will
renovate and move into 6,770 square feet in the former Kirby Auto
Parts building, constructed in 1955. (Bhatt, Palm Beach Post)
