one-run, six-inning perfromance against the Mets. How the Braves
have beaten him three times is a mystery. He has pitched carrer 26
innings against Atlanta, given up three earned runs and still has a
1-3 lifetime record against the Braves. The Braves last defeated
him 3-1 at Turner Field April 16. Neagle should improve over his
last start, or heaven help him. Stuck without an effective
changeup, Neagle was ravaged for eight hits and nine runs by the
Cubs last Monday in the worst start of his career and the worst by
a Braves starter in six years. He has been encouraged by his recent
side sessions and is determined to throw more breaking balls this
time, a pitch he simply forgot to use against the Cubs. The Pirates
are a challenge for him. The Pittsburgh crowds have been hard on
him when he returns to his old town and the bulk of the Pirate
order _ Jason Kendall, Jose Guillen, Tony Womack and Kevin Young _
have a combined .394 career average against him.
</P>
