LISTS (Undated) - Every columnist in America seems to be writing
about the Modern Library list of the 100 best English-language
novels of the past 100 years. It's almost obligatory.
</P>
<P>
   The only thing they seem to agree on is that James Joyce's
``Ulysses'' is hard to read. But they have missed the real
significance of the list. And that is that Americans don't actually
read the books, but instead read the list. With LISTS-LIST. By
RICHARD NILSEN. Story moved in the ``E`` category. &QL; 
