College campus in order to finish his degree following his NBA
career. He left in 1982 after his junior year, 12 courses shy of a
sociology degree. ``To me, if I was going to go back to school,
this is where I wanted to go,'' says Bagley, 38, who deliberately
reentered academia at a slow pace, knowing it would take him a
while to get reacquainted with its rhythms. (Jim Davis/Boston Globe
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) UNDATED -- July 24, 1998 -- LOBSTER-DEPLETE-BOS, 7-24 --
Fisherman Chuck Houghton repairs lobster traps before leaving the
dock to head out to sea. Lobster, New England's most valuable
seafood, has been a godsend to depressed fishing communities,
providing record catches at a time when overfishing has decimated
other fish populations. Now, biologists warn that the lobster trap
``arms race'' has pushed the lobster population to the brink of
collapse. (David L. Ryan/Boston Globe Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) LOS ANGELES -- July 24, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JULY 26 --
ABOUT-CARS-ELECTRIC-2, 7-24 -- The Honda EV Plus remote offers a
battery check, left; filling the Honda at a public charger. The
four-seat hatchback looks like a small minivan and leases for $455
a month. (Jill Connelly/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) UNDATED -- July 24, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JULY 26 --
ABOUT-CARS-ELECTRIC-1, 7-24 -- From top, the Honda EV Plus offers a
utilitarian body with the look of a small mini-van (Jill
Connelly/New York Times Photo); the Toyota RAV4-EV possesses a
range of 100 miles and top speed of 78 mph; the General Motors EV1
has the lowest range and the highest profile.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) BOSTON, Mass. -- July 24, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JULY 26
-- MUTFUND-ASIA, 7-24 -- ``We almost seek out areas of high
perceived risk,'' says Mark Madden, the manager of the Pioneer
Emerging Markets fund. Despite the financial crisis in Asia, 49
percent of the fund is in Asian stocks. (Ed Quinn/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
