<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
(HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
  c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dundee Realty Corp., Toronto, plans to sell all of its
residential revenue properties and all of its commercial revenue
properties in the United States and to close its property office in
Dallas by the end of next month.
</P>
<P>
   Coca-Cola Co., Atlanta, bought a 15 percent stake in National
Beverage Co., a bottler based in Ramallah in the West Bank, which
will distribute the world's largest soft drink company's sodas in
the West Bank and Gaza Strip. Terms were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Ross Technology Co., Austin, Texas, which makes and sells
microprocessors, plans to sell its remaining assets and lay off 148
employees.
</P>
